1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Aslan, today your heart will roar.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Wow, that's right.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
By the way, Marinette never falls in love with a statue.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,000
You know I'm not good with girls.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,000
This happened all of a sudden, you know.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Should I go over to my friend and play a prank?

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Should I give a compliment?

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Should I call you to the zoo?

9
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Should I be serious?

10
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Nino, I think you're overthinking it.

11
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,000
A zoo?

12
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Are you serious?

13
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Ah! Yeah. They say there are some really weird animals.

14
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Listen, just be yourself.

15
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Easy for you to say, Mr. Cover Model of Young Fashion Magazine.

16
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,000
I'm not cool.

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
You're pretty cool yourself, my friend. Trust me.

18
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Otherwise, you wouldn't be my best friend.

19
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
The zoo is nice.

20
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
He's definitely coming. Trust me.

21
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
What if I act like a goofball around you?

22
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:01,000
She doesn't want me anyway. If they think I'm a loser, it's fine, I'm here for you.

23
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Yeah, totally. Don't you think so too?

24
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,000
I'm not taking him from there.

25
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Let's go to Germany already.

26
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
I agree. Okay.

27
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
How smart and handsome he is!

28
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Someone who takes care of themselves and is sweet like candy, you know.

29
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Almost all of them. Oh, sorry about that, right Nino?

30
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Sorry. >> Sorryyy. >> Srry.

31
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Sorry about that. How can we make it up to you?

32
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Got any ideas, Nino?

33
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
I'm thinking, should we go to the zoo together?

34
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:44,000
I heard there's a new guy there, and they say there's a panther too.

35
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Great idea. Isn't it?

36
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,000
You really love it.

37
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Oh yeah, I really love animals.

38
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Oh man, what an idiot.

39
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Oh man, what an animal.

40
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Yeah, I like them.

41
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Great. How about 4 o'clock after school?

42
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Is Nino okay with it?

43
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Great. So, 4:00 then.

44
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
At 4 o'clock, at 4:00.

45
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Yeah. >> Oh, the kid you're crazy about just asked you out, if you noticed.

46
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Isn't it?

47
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Yeah. Oh wait.

48
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,000
What? No, not today.

49
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
No way today.

50
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,000
I haven't washed my hair yet.

51
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
I didn't wear my lucky socks.

52
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Alya, help out. I can't do it alone. Please help me.

53
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
So, how'd you pull that off, buddy?

54
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Like I said, you bring this on yourself.

55
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Of course, if I can just be myself.

56
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
It hadn't worked before anyway.

57
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,000
You're definitely talking nonsense. Of course you can.

58
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Or when you're all alone at the zoo.

59
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
So, that doesn't work when we're alone either, buddy.

60
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
You should come too.

61
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
You can't leave me alone, though. No problem, Nino.

62
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:51,000
We're friends after all. Just a little test.

63
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Can you hear me?

64
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
I can hear it, but I still don't think I can pull it off.

65
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Of course you can. Just be yourself.

66
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,000
You know what happened last time.

67
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Just be yourself, Marinette.

68
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Hey! What are you up to?

69
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Hey guys, can you come out?

70
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Go outside. Alright, now just be yourself and figure out how to get there.

71
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Where are you? My love.

72
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:23,000
If you can't even talk to her, how's she supposed to be the love of your life?

73
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Just don't show up in the middle of things.

74
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,000
I'll talk to him, you'll see.

75
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,000
I need to talk to him. Yeah, that's totally right.

76
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,000
This is what motivation looks like. Yep, here they come.

77
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Hey Marinette. >> Oh, wrong alarm.

78
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Hey there, I'm Max.

79
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
What are you looking for here?

80
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
They said a new panther had arrived. I'll see who has better leg muscles.

81
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Would you have come too?

82
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
The target is 10 o'clock to the right.

83
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
No, thanks, it's not necessary.

84
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
I'm waiting for someone. You guys go ahead.

85
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Alright. Maybe we'll catch up later.

86
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Yeah, see you. >> Where's Adrien? >> Don't know.

87
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Hey Nino.

88
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Isn't Adrien with you?

89
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Well, it'd probably be better if I weren't around.

90
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
It's better if it doesn't happen.

91
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:17,000
This trip is turning out to be more fun than I thought.

92
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Turn up the volume. Otherwise, it just won't work.

93
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
We can still hang out even if Adrien isn't around, right?

94
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Sure, we can hang out, you goof.

95
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
So, wasn't he coming either?

96
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Can't we just wait for him?

97
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Tell him you want to be alone with him.

98
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Not yet. >> What did you say?

99
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Yeah, you're right.

100
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Let's wait. Hey, why are you talking?

101
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Don't wait for me. I'm not coming.

102
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Look, dad, guess what I brought you.

103
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:45,000
The best for my baby.

104
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Wow, check out how big that piece of meat he's eating is!

105
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Food that animals who can run faster than 100 kilometers per hour always eat.

106
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
So, is it like 100 kilometers or what?

107
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Is that all?

108
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,000
I thought panthers were faster.

109
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
I'm sure I can beat him.

110
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Impossible. No one can outrun a panther.

111
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Oh yeah? So, what place did the cat you're talking about get in the state track meet?

112
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,000
I came in first.

113
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:14,000
You can never compare yourself to a panther, kid.

114
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,000
No need. I'm way better looking than him anyway.

115
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Let's see: if wind blows at 2 meters per second behind you and the sun hits at 45 degrees from the northeast...

116
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
I don't think you'd be a rotten egg.

117
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
You'd become bait for it.

118
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Your friend is right, kid. Now go on.

119
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,000
He wants to be alone while eating.

120
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Don't make him angry. >> Angry, ma'am? We're talking about a panther, a wild animal.

121
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Get lost, or I'll have you kicked out of the zoo.

122
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Come on, Max. Let's leave this poor kitty with his grumpy keeper.

123
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:02,000
See, release the animal inside you.

124
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
I like that idea.

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Fly, my little akuma.

126
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Go and capture the zookeeper. Go on.

127
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,000
I don't think he's willing to come.

128
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Huh, I don't think he's coming.

129
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,000
You think? Repeat what I said.

130
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Yes, he'll come, but first there's something you want to say.

131
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:34,000
And... yes, he'll come, but first there's something I want to tell you.

132
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,000
I actually love you.

133
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:41,000
I actually love... not you, someone else, but I can't say it.

134
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Hey! What are you doing?

135
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Oh really? Then let me help you.

136
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:50,000
Would you? >> Are you going to give expert advice on confessing to someone?

137
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,000
I'm really curious.

138
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
I'm really curious.

139
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,000
What? >> Well, I'm really curious about this lucky girl.

140
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Oh yes. It's you, isn't it? >> That's your friend Alya.

141
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
What? >> Alya?

142
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
That's great. >> No.

143
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
No. That's not great at all.

144
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,000
I can set you up if you want.

145
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
What did you say? Are you serious?

146
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
You didn't even ask me first.

147
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Uh, Nino is like a brother to me.

148
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
No, the discussion is closed.

149
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,000
But if you refuse, he'll be really upset.

150
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Did you say something?

151
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
I said it would be really sad if you don't tell him.

152
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,000
Keeper, I am Hawk Moth.

153
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:43,000
I'll give you power in exchange for a little favor.

154
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Yes, Hawk Moth.

155
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Hey, little one, still up for the race?

156
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Don't stop, I'm giving you a head start.

157
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
That's mine.

158
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,000
I absolutely refuse to go out with Nino.

159
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Mind control. Get out of here! What is this?

160
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,000
We'd better go.

161
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,000
Alya, why didn't you listen, Marinette?

162
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Ah, I couldn't help myself.

163
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,000
I didn't want Nino to be sad.

164
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
We'll sort that out later.

165
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Now you have to transform.

166
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:38,000
One catch. There's something we have to do.

167
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Black Claws. You lost, kid.

168
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,000
See that? How do you like the panther?

169
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Is that all you've got?

170
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,000
What do you think about ladybugs, then?

171
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,000
And a black cat.

172
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
I think I'm higher up the food chain.

173
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Keeper, take their jewels immediately.

174
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Their Miraculouses, then bring them to me.

175
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
If you care about yourself, get out of here now.

176
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Cat Noir. The akuma must be in his cuff.

177
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,000
You hold him.

178
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,000
I'll get the akuma.

179
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Attack. We need to put them all in cages.

180
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Oh, really?

181
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
I'm sure they won't resist you while you're doing that.

182
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,000
We'd better split up.

183
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Hey! What's this?

184
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Don't move, nothing will happen.

185
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
So? What's the news?

186
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
Oh, there are too many of them.

187
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,000
We can't hold them all. >> Then what can we do?

188
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Let's go back to Plan A.

189
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:30,000
If we destroy his cuff, I can catch the akuma and everything will go back to normal.

190
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Sounds like a good plan.

191
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,000
But this won't break... >> Actually.

192
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
He didn't break it either.

193
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Then how did he escape? I don't know, but who do we need to find?

194
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
I mean, we need to find that kid.

195
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Aha, there he is. >> Ha.

196
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:06,000
There are only two of us left, kid.

197
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Soon I'll be alone.

198
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,000
You won't get away this time.

199
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:17,000
Quick, go into the first building you see and hide.

200
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:20,000
You can't catch me. >> Now we know how he escaped.

201
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Who's where? It's fine.

202
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Little pest. Help, please help.

203
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
Uh, nothing's wrong, kid.

204
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,000
Come here now.

205
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:45,000
Slow down. >> He's safe inside the building.

206
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
Panthers can't open doors or get inside.

207
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:59,000
Maybe not panthers, but if he transforms into a smaller animal, like a mouse or... >> Right.

208
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,000
But we still have an advantage.

209
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
We know exactly where to find his prey.

210
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,000
The keeper will sniff him out very soon.

211
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
But in the meantime, we'll have time to make a plan.

212
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,000
We have to stop him before he turns Paris into a forest.

213
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Follow me. >> Hello, ma'am.

214
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:27,000
B-but you're Ladybug.

215
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Oh yes, I am.

216
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
We interrupt our broadcast for a special news report.

217
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Animals are taking over Paris.

218
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,000
Police are trying to get the situation under control.

219
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,000
For your safety, stay home and remain calm.

220
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:45,000
Mayor Bourgeois will address the public shortly. >> You're safe in here.

221
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,000
Can I have this?

222
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
Oh, sure. >> Come on, Cat Noir.

223
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,000
Lock all the windows and doors.

224
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,000
We'll handle the rest.

225
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:57,000
You won't be in danger. >> Thank you, sir.

226
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,000
Thank you. >> You're welcome.

227
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
Ladybug. >> That's it.

228
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Hey, what's this?

229
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Air freshener. With this, he won't be able to smell us.

230
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,000
Thanks. I've always wanted to smell like...

231
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Ocean breeze. >> Can't we trap him somewhere inside?

232
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Only if he turns into something big.

233
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Oh! Oh! Is this cage big enough?

234
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Definitely. But how do we get him inside?

235
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
He's coming. >> It's working.

236
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Whose scent is he picking up?

237
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Come with me. >> Ladybug, you thought well.

238
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Couldn't it have been a slower animal?

239
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Where's the button for these doors?

240
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Oh! Of course none of them work.

241
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,000
The keys. Get their Miraculouses.

242
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Face to face. He's getting tired from changing so much.

243
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Then let him get even more tired.

244
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
We'll be able to catch his akuma easily.

245
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:16,000
Cat Noir. This doesn't really count as a cage, but it'll work.

246
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:36,000
I think he absolutely can't stand listening to this sound.

247
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,000
You're unbearable too.

248
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:42,000
Now let's wait. Ready for the akuma?

249
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,000
It's working. >> Hey!

250
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Let's see if they count as endangered species.

251
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:12,000
T-Rex may have gone extinct long ago, but technically it's still an animal.

252
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,000
Looks like there will be two more endangered animals soon.

253
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,000
A cat and a ladybug.

254
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Lucky Charm. A hairdryer?

255
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Unfortunately, the keeper doesn't have a flat tire.

256
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:47,000
His forearms are so small.

257
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Bet he can't shoot hoops well.

258
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
What are you trying to say?

259
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:55,000
If you climb on top of him, he can't grab and push you, and while you distract him, I'll attack.

260
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,000
Sounds like a good plan.

261
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,000
I'm good at this.

262
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,000
It won't be easy. That was really weird.

263
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,000
We didn't need to use it.

264
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,000
I wonder what that means?

265
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:26,000
I think because we're a good team, we didn't need it.

266
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Cat Noir, wait.

267
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,000
I figured out what we're going to do.

268
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Ladybug... >> Enjoy your meal.

269
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,000
No, you'll pay for this.

270
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:03,000
You can't do evil anymore, little akuma.

271
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Give up the evil. That's it.

272
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,000
Goodbye, little butterfly.

273
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:19,000
Miraculous Ladybug.

274
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,000
Pound it! Ladybug, that was pretty tiring.

275
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Oh no! I have to go right away.

276
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
See you later. Cat Noir.

277
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,000
What happened to me?

278
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:49,000
Everything's fine, but check on the animals at the zoo.

279
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,000
You ruined everything, Ladybug.

280
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,000
It wasn't supposed to end like this.

281
00:18:54,000 --> 00:19:00,000
But I promise you, one day I'll be at the top of the food chain and I'll defeat you.

282
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Oh no, I completely forgot about Alya.

283
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,000
She's going to be so mad at me.

284
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:21,000
And what if she finds out you locked her in a cage with Nino?

285
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,000
Yeah. I think she might actually kill me.

286
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Getting angry is enough. Hey, listen Alya.

287
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
I'm sorry about what happened.

288
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
I shouldn't have told Nino you could meet up.

289
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:35,000
I wasn't thinking, but I'll explain everything to him, I mean it.

290
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,000
Don't worry. I promise.

291
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
Do you forgive me?

292
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Ha. >> Thank you, Nino.

293
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
Do you want one too, Marinette?

294
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
What's this doing here?

295
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Today, Ladybug locked both of us in the same cage.

296
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,000
And apparently we actually have a lot in common.

297
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Marinette, remember that girl I liked?

298
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,000
Oh yes. >> Well, it was actually you.

299
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Huh. >> Or so I thought, but after spending all this time with Alya... >> Okay, we don't need to give all the details, do we?

300
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Oh yes, sorry.

301
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,000
The funny thing is, it was actually Adrien who was coaching Nino from the start.

302
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
Huh. Adrien was there?

303
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,000
Yes. Great. Here.

304
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:18,000
He told me you liked someone.

305
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,000
He has no idea who it is.

306
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:24,000
I promise, because I don't speak for other people.

307
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
But if you want, I can arrange something.

308
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Of course, if I know who it is.

309
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Nino. >> Okay. You didn't hear anything.

310
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,000
You can talk to me if you want, Nino.